The National Security Strategy (NSS) released by President Donald J. Trump reflects his belief in putting America first and renewing confidence in the country both domestically and internationally. The strategy is based on four pillars, which include protecting the homeland, promoting American prosperity, preserving peace through strength, and advancing American influence. The NSS emphasizes a return to principled realism, acknowledging the importance of power in global affairs and the role of sovereign states in maintaining peace. It also highlights the promotion of American values as crucial for spreading peace and prosperity worldwide. President Trump's ultimate goal is to leave future generations with a stronger, better, and greater nation.